cs.CV, cs.BIO, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.HC 

The paper deals with iris recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). It also involves the study of eye diseases and their impact on iris recognition, which falls under the category of bioinformatics (cs.BIO). The use of algorithms for iris recognition and the analysis of their performance is a topic of interest in computer security (cs.CR). The collection and analysis of a large dataset of iris images involves multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspects.
